Package com.sabres

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    CountCallback
    A CountCallback is used to run code after a SabresQuery is used to count objects matching a query in a background thread.
    DeleteCallback
    A DeleteCallback is used to run code after deleting a SabresObject in a background thread.
    FetchCallback
    A FetchCallback is used to run code after fetching a SabresObject in a background thread.
    FindCallback<T extends SabresObject>
    A FindCallback is used to run code after a SabresQuery is used to find objects matching a query in a background thread.
    GetCallback<T extends SabresObject>
    A GetCallback is used to run code after a SabresQuery is used to get a SabresObject in a background thread.
    SaveCallback
    A SaveCallback is used to run code after saving a SabresObject in a background thread.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    Sabres
    The Sabres class contains static functions that handle global configuration and debug faculties for the Sabres library.
    SabresObject
    The SabresObject is a base class that allows custom objects to be saved and retrieved with the Sabres library.
    SabresQuery<T extends SabresObject>
    The SabresQuery class defines a query that is used to fetch SabresObjects.
  • Exception Summary 
    Exception Description
    SabresException
    A SabresException gets raised whenever a SabresObject issues an invalid request, such as deleting or editing an object that no longer exists in the database.
